1. What is TypeScript?

TypeScript (TS) is a superset of JavaScript created by Microsoft.
It adds:
Static typing
Interfaces
Generics

⚠️ JavaScript ⚠️
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
Problem:
You can pass anything.
add("5", 10) // "510"

⚠️ TypeScript ⚠️
function add(a: number, b: number): number {
  return a + b;
}
Now this will error:
add("5", 10)

