Interface

1. Used mainly to describe the structure of objects or classes.
interface User {
  name: string
  age: number
}

2. interface User {
  name: string
}

interface User {
  age: number
}

const person: User = {
  name: "Akash",
  age: 25
}

Type

Used to define any kind of type: primitives, unions, tuples, objects, etc.

type User = {
  name: string
  age: number
}
